id: pm-i6pi
title: "GH-590: cycle-creating blocked_by mutations succeed silently — items deadlock out of pm next with no inline feedback"
description: "GitHub issue #590: a dependency mutation that closes a blocked_by cycle exits 0 with no warning; both items permanently leave pm next ready/recommended and only pm graph audit (ordering_cycle) or pm deps (cycle:true) explain why — nothing points there. Parent-cycle mutations already fail fast (precedent); ordering-kind dep mutations must warn inline naming the cycle path (or reject with an override flag), consistent with that precedent."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: agent-ux,data-integrity,graph
created_at: "2026-07-18T10:08:29.551Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T13:14:16.500Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-18T12:14:07.856Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "Mutation that would create an ordering-kind dependency cycle warns inline with the cycle path and pm graph audit pointer, or rejects with an explicit override flag; parent-cycle fail-fast precedent cited in contract docs; existing stored legacy cycles unaffected; regression coverage for update/update-many/create --dep paths"
parent: pm-96h7
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: fixed
expected_result: Creating or updating an ordering dependency cycle warns inline with a concrete cycle path and graph-audit recovery while existing legacy cycles are not re-reported.
actual_result: "Create, update, and update-many compare immutable graph snapshots through the public SDK primitive and emit ordering_cycle_created only for newly introduced cycles containing the changed item."
