  "2026-07-18T13:13:53.348Z",codex-gpt5,"CodeRabbit review evidence: accepted the exact-head concurrency finding on PR #593. Single-item update cycle advisories now refresh the target row from the locked pre-mutation document before applying dependency changes, preventing racing target updates from causing false or suppressed cycle warnings. A real lock-contention test mutates the target while runUpdate waits, then proves the pre-existing cycle is not misreported as new. Focused 103-test update suite, lint/zero-duplication, TypeScript, static/docstring/package/token gates, and full 310-file/5,908-test coverage at 100/100/100/100 pass."
